)=== \n{{Episode table |background=#FCC767 |overall= |season= |title= |director= |writer= |aux2= |aux2T=Storyboard by |airdate= |prodcode= |viewers= |country=U.S. |episodes =\n{{Episode table/part|p=[[Nicktoons (United States)|Nicktoons]]{{Efn|This season first began airing on Nickelodeon Africa on September 17, 2018.}}|c=#FCC767|nopart=y}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 21\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| DirectedBy      = Tahir Rana\n| WrittenBy       = Adam Cohen and Michael Pecoriello\n| Aux2            = Bram Cayne and Will Jeyasingham\n| Title           = We're Gonna Need a Bigger Cup\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|5|3}}\n| ProdCode        = 201\n| Viewers         = 0.10\n| ShortSummary    = Tony Stanza insists the kids take a break without their tech just when a new WP called Eraser Face appears and tries to erase the Wayne.\n| LineColor       = FCC767\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 22\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| DirectedBy      = Tahir Rana\n| WrittenBy       = Stacey Greenberger and Michael Pecoriello\n| Aux2            = Matt Wilson\n| Title           = Welcome to the Wassermans\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|5|3}}\n| ProdCode        = 202\n| Viewers         = 0.12\n| ShortSummary    = A sleepover at Wendell's turns into a mission to get a mysterious jewel from his teenage sister and a battle with a werewolf.\n| LineColor       = FCC767\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 23\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| DirectedBy      = Tahir Rana \n| WrittenBy       = Jeffrey Sayers and Michael Pecoriello\n| Aux2            = Bram Cayne\n| Title           = An Olly-Day Miracle!\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|5|10}}\n| ProdCode        = 203\n| Viewers         = 0.07\n| ShortSummary    = Olly spends his made-up holiday, Olly Day, with the Arcsine to try and show her how to have fun.  \n| LineColor       = FCC767\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 24\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| DirectedBy      = Tahir Rana \n| WrittenBy       = Jacob Fleisher, Billy Lopez, and Michael Pecoriello \n| Aux2            = Matt Wilson\n| Title           = That's Squidjit Bowling\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|5|10}}\n| ProdCode        = 204\n| Viewers         = 0.05\n| ShortSummary    = When Dennis is unable to compete in the Squidjit Bowling Championship, Ansi and John Keats step in to play for him against the undefeated HuMannequins.\n| LineColor       = FCC767\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 25\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n| DirectedBy      = Tahir Rana\n| WrittenBy       = Adam Cohen and Michael Pecoriello\n| Aux2            = Aisha Ghali and Firas Momani\n| Title           = We're the Wayniacs\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|5|17}}\n| ProdCode        = 205\n| Viewers         = 0.13\n| ShortSummary    = A heavy metal Wayne phenomenon called C.C. Scratch attempts to turn everyone into musical instruments, so Olly, Ansi and Katherine Alice form a rock band to defeat it. \n| LineColor       = FCC767\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 26\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| DirectedBy      = Tahir Rana\n| WrittenBy       = Jeffrey Sayers and Michael Pecoriello\n| Aux2            = Will Jeyasingham\n| Title           = Curious Brains of the Wayne\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|5|17}}\n| ProdCode        = 206\n| Viewers         = 0.15\n| ShortSummary    = While looking for something to present at the annual Wayne science fair, Olly accidentally transforms himself into a fly. While he is in insect form, he must try to prevent the Spy from using Saraline's project to steal the Arcsine's powers.\n| LineColor       = FCC767\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 27\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| DirectedBy      = Tahir Rana\n| WrittenBy       = Erica Ottenberg and Michael Pecoriello\n| Aux2            = Bram Cayne and Caroline Hung\n| Title           = Wiles Styles You Over\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|5|24}}\n| ProdCode        = 207\n| Viewers         = 0.17\n| ShortSummary    = Julia gives Olly, 