{"title_page": "Henri Abadie", "text_new": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Henri Abadie\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1963|2|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Tarbes]], [[France]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| currentteam    = \n| discipline     = \n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = \n}}\n'''Henri Abadie''' (born 13 February 1963) is a French former professional [[cycle sport|racing cyclist]].<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite web |url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/Henri_Abadie |title=Henri Abadie |accessdate=30 March 2015 |work=Pro Cycling Stats}}</ref> He rode in two editions of the [[Tour de France]], two editions of the [[Giro d'Italia]] and one edition of the [[Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|11}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Abadie, Henri}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Tarbes]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a cyclists]]\n{{France-cycling-bio-1960s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Henri Abadie\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1963|2|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Tarbes]], [[France]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| currentteam    = \n| discipline     = \n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = \n}}\n'''Henri Abadie''' (born 13 February 1963) is a French former professional [[cycle sport|racing cyclist]].<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite web |url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/Henri_Abadie |title=Henri Abadie |accessdate=30 March 2015 |work=Pro Cycling Stats}}</ref> He rode in two editions of the [[Tour de France]], two editions of the [[Giro d'Italia]] and one edition of the [[Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|11}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Abadie, Henri}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:People from Tarbes]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a cyclists]]\n{{France-cycling-bio-1960s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henri_Abadie"}
